    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">651.116 Nitrate/81: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 18, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> publishes Paris despatch that United
                    States has been shut out of French nitrate market this year, Chile and Norway
                    receiving 80,000 and 20,000 tons respectively. If appropriate at this stage,
                    please take matter up with French again, emphasizing this Government’s position
                    as outlined in Department’s 469, November 21, 1934.<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d196fn40">
                        <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_214">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., p. 214</ref>.</note> Please advise
                    Department by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
